ble format.","position":{"start":{"line":8,"column":1},"end":{"line":8,"column":1}},"key":"bCE4rfg6XN"}],"key":"iH4eKp4nEo"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":10,"column":1},"end":{"line":10,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"What is Magic Harvest ?","position":{"start":{"line":10,"column":1},"end":{"line":10,"column":1}},"key":"Q0jNrO3f4I"}],"identifier":"what-is-magic-harvest","label":"What is Magic Harvest ?","html_id":"what-is-magic-harvest","implicit":true,"key":"GUD5krj2Nd"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":12,"column":1},"end":{"line":12,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":12,"column":1},"end":{"line":12,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Magic Harvest is a small extension that I develloped during my PhD thesis","position":{"start":{"line":12,"column":1},"end":{"line":12,"column":1}},"key":"d6yG0ah55A"}],"key":"agGMkzZ0TT"},{"type":"text","value":". My work required me to compare the effect of several forest management scenarios in LANDIS-II; but at the time, LANDIS-II lacked several important features that I needed to implement forest management in the model. I created Magic Harvest in order to solve the issue.","position":{"start":{"line":12,"column":1},"end":{"line":12,"column":1}},"key":"fWlAkNMumD"}],"key":"rC5HLPHWX2"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":14,"column":1},"end":{"line":14,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"image","url":"https://klemet.github.io/Workshop-MagicHarvest//build/Slide2-d933c09c9ef9b6626a9ffc4f832be593.jpg","position":{"start":{"line":14,"column":1},"end":{"line":14,"column":1}},"key":"LAxmNLwaHo","urlSource":"./images/Slide2.jpg"}],"key":"rstZiTe12i"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":16,"column":1},"end":{"line":16,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":16,"column":1},"end":{"line":16,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The Magic Harvest extension is both simple and complicated","position":{"start":{"line":16,"column":1},"end":{"line":16,"column":1}},"key":"a6UCj1RoSh"}],"key":"OPocnWCOh1"},{"type":"text","value":". Simple, because its functionning can be summarized in two sentences : it’s a companion extension for Biomass Harvest (the main harvest extension for LANDIS-II; the other ones are almost never used) who’s goal is to run before Biomass Harvest. ","position":{"start":{"line":16,"column":1},"end":{"line":16,"column":1}},"key":"cdkod7taFq"},{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":16,"column":1},"end":{"line":16,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"When running, it will simply launch a custom command defined by the user - for example an R or Python script - and will then force Biomass Harvest to re-load its parameters","position":{"start":{"line":16,"column":1},"end":{"line":16,"column":1}},"key":"IIwEFwPBCA"}],"key":"kvzcHomRvg"},{"type":"text","value":". That’s it.","position":{"start":{"line":16,"column":1},"end":{"line":16,"column":1}},"key":"mSr9PEO8tx"}],"key":"pQNZxMnE3z"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":18,"column":1},"end":{"line":18,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The complex part is understanding the consequences of this and learning to play with it. The consequences is that we can control what Biomass Harvest does at different degrees : complete and total control, or still letting Biomass Harvest do some choices based on its own algorithm. Learning to play with Magic Harvest mostly means learning to write scripts that will do what you want to do.","position":{"start":{"line":18,"column":1},"end":{"line":18,"column":1}},"key":"QhiQq10Jgp"}],"key":"T97FOm9Sdr"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":21,"column":1},"end":{"line":21,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Plan of the workshop","position":{"start":{"line":21,"column":1},"end":{"line":21,"column":1}},"key":"L1glHZRa2f"}],"identifier":"plan-of-the-workshop","label":"Plan 